hackman - the package manager for hackers
    Manage software packages from a wide range of binary and source formats
    in a highly sandboxed, modular way with an emphasis on user-level deployment.

Inspirations:
    nix, module (http://modules.sourceforge.net/), apt, cabal, cpan

hypothetical use cases:
    # install a package from some random website
    $ hackman install http://somesite.net/moo-1.2.3.tar.bz2
    
    # then uninstall it because it sucks
    $ hackman uninstall moo-1.2.3
    
    # list the available packages
    $ hackman avail
    
    # list the loaded packages
    $ hackman list
    
    # bundle a package moo with its dependencies for remote deployment
    $ hackman bundle moo.hackman
